---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy | Next Metro"
  description="Privacy information for Next Metro, the app for knowing when to leave for the next train."
>
  <section class="section tight content-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy that stays out of your way.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Next Metro is designed to help you time your trip without turning your
      commute into a profile.
    </p>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        Next Metro does not require an account. The app may use the station,
        route, and timing preferences you choose so it can show relevant train
        information on your device.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Location</h2>
      <p>
        If the app requests location access, it is used to help estimate nearby
        stations or commute timing. You can change location permissions at any
        time in your device settings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        Next Metro may rely on transit data providers to display arrival
        information. Those providers can update schedules, predictions, or
        service details independently from the app.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:support@nextmetro.app">support@nextmetro.app</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
